      "system": {
        "description": "<p><strong>Energy Drain: </strong>A successfully hit target must save or gain 1d6 system strain. If this would take the target over their maximum, they instead permanently loses one experience level (or Hit Die). This incurs a loss of one Hit Die of hit points, as well as all other benefits due to the drained level (e.g. spells, saving throws, etc.). A character&rsquo;s XP is reduced to halfway between the former and new levels. A person drained of all levels becomes a wight in 1d4 days, under the control of the wight that killed them.</p>",
